Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language.
Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991.
automation, web development, data science, and cybersecurity.

Why Python for Offensive Security?
Readable syntax for quick scripting
Powerful standard libraries and third-party tools (e.g., scapy, requests, pwntools)
Cross-platform: works on Linux, Windows, and macOS
Ideal for automating tasks, building custom exploits, and developing post-exploitation tools


task of the day 
Setting Up an IDE Recommended environments for coding:

VS Code (with Python extension)
PyCharm (Community Edition is free)
Jupyter Notebooks (for interactive scripts and demos)
Thonny (great for beginners)
